The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has introduced a state-of-the-art Parallel Voting Tabulation (PVT) system to check any form of rigging in this Saturday’s presidential election. The PVT is a scientifically proven, best practice technique, to hold election authorities accountable, particularly, when there is a lack of trust and the results are highly contested. Addressing a press conference on Wednesday in Abuja, the spokesman and   Chairman Strategy Committee of the PDP Presidential Campaign Organisation, Osita Chidoka said “if the election is rigged, there would be consequences.”  Details later… 2019: PDP rejects nationwide military 'Operation Python Dance' BMO: PDP engaged ‘Russian hackers’ to rig 2019 elections PDP asks Prince Charles to speak to Buhari on 2019